{"format":"tiptap/v1","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Semantic HTML means choosing elements based on what the content "},{"type":"text","text":"means","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]},{"type":"text","text":", not just how it looks. A "},{"type":"text","text":"<div>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is a generic container with no meaning; a "},{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is a container that explicitly means \"navigation links\". Browsers, screen readers, search engines, and browser extensions all read semantic meaning to decide how to present and index your content. Writing semantic HTML is one of the most impactful things you can do for accessibility and search engine optimization — and it costs nothing extra."}]},{"type":"image","attrs":{"src":"data:image/svg+xml;base64,","alt":"Semantic HTML (header, main, article, aside, footer) compared to non-semantic div soup","title":null}},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Semantics Matter"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider a screen reader encountering a page full of "},{"type":"text","text":"<div>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" elements. It cannot determine which is the main content, which is navigation, which is a sidebar. A user who navigates by landmarks or headings is stuck — they must read everything sequentially."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now consider the same page built with "},{"type":"text","text":"<header>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<main>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<article>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<aside>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","text":"<footer>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":". Screen readers present a landmark menu, letting users jump directly to the main content, skip repeated navigation, or go straight to the footer. This is the difference between a usable and an unusable experience for millions of people with disabilities."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Search engines also benefit. Google uses "},{"type":"text","text":"<article>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to identify primary content, "},{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to find internal links, and heading hierarchies ("},{"type":"text","text":"<h1>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":"–"},{"type":"text","text":"<h6>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":") to understand the document outline. These signals affect crawling, indexing, and ranking."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Structural Landmark Elements"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTML5 introduced landmark elements that correspond to identifiable regions of a page:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Element"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Role"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key constraint"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<header>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Site or section header"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can appear inside article/section; not just page-level"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigation links"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use aria-label when multiple nav elements exist"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<main>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Primary page content"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Exactly one per page"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<article>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-contained content unit"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Should make sense standalone (blog post, forum reply)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<section>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Thematic content group"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Should have its own heading; not a generic wrapper"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<aside>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tangentially related content"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sidebars, pull quotes, related links"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<footer>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Closing content"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can appear inside article/section too"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"header"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","text":"<header>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" element represents introductory content for its nearest ancestor sectioning element or the page. It typically contains a logo, site title, and primary navigation."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<header>\n  <a href=\"/\" aria-label=\"Home\">\n    <img src=\"/logo.svg\" alt=\"Acme Inc\" width=\"120\" height=\"40\">\n  </a>\n  <nav aria-label=\"Main navigation\">\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"/products\">Products</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/blog\">Blog</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/about\">About</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </nav>\n</header>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","text":"<header>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" inside an "},{"type":"text","text":"<article>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" scopes to that article — it is not the page header:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<article>\n  <header>\n    <h2>Article Title</h2>\n    <p>By <a href=\"/author/alice\">Alice</a> ·\n       <time datetime=\"2025-06-15\">June 15, 2025</time></p>\n  </header>\n  <p>Article body...</p>\n</article>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"nav"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" only for major navigation blocks — primary site nav, breadcrumbs, pagination. Do not wrap every list of links in "},{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":". When a page has multiple "},{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" elements, each must have a distinct "},{"type":"text","text":"aria-label","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" so screen reader users can tell them apart."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- Site navigation -->\n<nav aria-label=\"Main navigation\">\n  <ul>\n    <li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"/about\">About</a></li>\n  </ul>\n</nav>\n\n<!-- Breadcrumb navigation -->\n<nav aria-label=\"Breadcrumb\">\n  <ol>\n    <li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"/blog\">Blog</a></li>\n    <li aria-current=\"page\">This Post</li>\n  </ol>\n</nav>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"main"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A page has exactly one "},{"type":"text","text":"<main>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" element. It wraps the primary content — the part unique to this page, not repeated across pages (like navigation and footer)."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<body>\n  <header>...</header>\n  <main id=\"main-content\">\n    <h1>Blog: The Case for Semantic HTML</h1>\n    <article>...</article>\n  </main>\n  <footer>...</footer>\n</body>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Skip to content\" links — the "},{"type":"text","text":"<a href=\"#main-content\">Skip to main content</a>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" found as the first element on many pages — target "},{"type":"text","text":"<main>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":". They let keyboard and screen reader users bypass repeated header navigation."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"article"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"text","text":"<article>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is content that could stand alone and be redistributed — a blog post, a news story, a product card, a forum reply, an email in a webmail client. If the content makes sense extracted from the page, it is an article."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<main>\n  <article>\n    <header>\n      <h1>Understanding Semantic HTML</h1>\n      <p><time datetime=\"2025-06-15\">June 15, 2025</time></p>\n    </header>\n    <p>Semantic HTML is...</p>\n    <section>\n      <h2>Why it matters</h2>\n      <p>...</p>\n    </section>\n    <footer>\n      <p>Tags: <a href=\"/tag/html\">HTML</a>,\n                <a href=\"/tag/accessibility\">Accessibility</a></p>\n    </footer>\n  </article>\n</main>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"section"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","text":"<section>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is a thematic grouping of content that typically has its own heading. It is not a generic wrapper — use "},{"type":"text","text":"<div>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" for that. If a "},{"type":"text","text":"<section>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" has no heading, consider whether it should be a "},{"type":"text","text":"<div>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<article>\n  <h1>CSS Layout Methods</h1>\n  <section>\n    <h2>Flexbox</h2>\n    <p>Flexbox is for one-dimensional layouts...</p>\n  </section>\n  <section>\n    <h2>Grid</h2>\n    <p>Grid is for two-dimensional layouts...</p>\n  </section>\n</article>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"aside"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"text","text":"<aside>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" holds content tangentially related to the surrounding content — sidebars, pull quotes, glossary terms, related links, promotional content. \"Tangentially related\" means it could be removed without making the main content less coherent."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<main>\n  <article>\n    <h1>Introduction to Next.js</h1>\n    <p>Next.js is a React framework...</p>\n    <aside>\n      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Basic React knowledge</li>\n        <li>Node.js installed</li>\n      </ul>\n    </aside>\n    <p>The main article continues here...</p>\n  </article>\n</main>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"footer"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","text":"<footer>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" contains closing information about its nearest sectioning ancestor — authorship, copyright, related links, contact info. Like "},{"type":"text","text":"<header>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", it can appear inside "},{"type":"text","text":"<article>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","text":"<section>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" elements, not only at the bottom of the page."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<footer>\n  <p>&copy; 2025 Acme Inc. All rights reserved.</p>\n  <nav aria-label=\"Footer links\">\n    <a href=\"/privacy\">Privacy</a>\n    <a href=\"/terms\">Terms</a>\n    <a href=\"/contact\">Contact</a>\n  </nav>\n</footer>"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Text-Level Semantic Elements"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Landmark elements structure the page. Text-level semantic elements convey the meaning of inline content:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Element"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Meaning"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Do not confuse with"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<strong>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Strong importance"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<b>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — bold styling only, no meaning"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<em>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Stress emphasis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<i>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — italic styling only, no meaning"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<time>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Machine-readable date/time"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Plain text date strings"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<abbr>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Abbreviation with expansion"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Acronyms written out in running text"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<cite>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title of a creative work"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Author names (use plain text)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<code>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inline code fragment"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<pre>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — preformatted block"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<kbd>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Keyboard input"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<code>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — not for key presses"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<mark>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Highlighted/relevant text"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decorative highlights"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<del>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" / "},{"type":"text","text":"<ins>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deleted / inserted text"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Strikethrough styling"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- strong: important, not just visually bold -->\n<p>Warning: <strong>do not delete this file</strong> — it is required at runtime.</p>\n\n<!-- em: stress emphasis that changes meaning -->\n<p>I said you should go <em>now</em>, not tomorrow.</p>\n\n<!-- time: machine-readable date -->\n<p>Published on <time datetime=\"2025-06-15\">June 15, 2025</time>.</p>\n\n<!-- abbr: expand abbreviations on first use -->\n<p><abbr title=\"Cascading Style Sheets\">CSS</abbr> controls visual presentation.</p>\n\n<!-- cite: title of a creative work -->\n<p>Inspired by <cite>The Elements of Typographic Style</cite>.</p>\n\n<!-- kbd: key press -->\n<p>Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>S</kbd> to save.</p>\n\n<!-- mark: search result highlight -->\n<p>Results for \"Next.js\": <mark>Next.js</mark> is a React framework...</p>\n\n<!-- del + ins: tracked changes -->\n<p>Price: <del>$199</del> <ins>$149</ins></p>"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Heading Hierarchy"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Headings ("},{"type":"text","text":"<h1>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":"–"},{"type":"text","text":"<h6>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":") create the document outline that screen readers present as a table of contents. The hierarchy must be logical and must not skip levels:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- ✅ Correct: logical nesting, no skipped levels -->\n<h1>Next.js Application Development</h1>\n  <h2>Routing</h2>\n    <h3>App Router</h3>\n    <h3>Pages Router</h3>\n  <h2>Data Fetching</h2>\n    <h3>Server Components</h3>\n    <h3>Client Components</h3>\n\n<!-- ❌ Incorrect: skips from h1 to h3 -->\n<h1>Next.js Application Development</h1>\n  <h3>Routing</h3>   <!-- missing h2 level -->\n  <h3>Data Fetching</h3>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each page should have exactly one "},{"type":"text","text":"<h1>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" describing the primary topic. Subsections use "},{"type":"text","text":"<h2>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", sub-subsections use "},{"type":"text","text":"<h3>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", and so on. Do not choose heading levels based on visual size — use CSS to control visual appearance."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In Next.js, the page's "},{"type":"text","text":"<h1>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" typically comes from the page component. The site name goes in "},{"type":"text","text":"<title>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (via metadata), not in an "},{"type":"text","text":"<h1>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" on every page — putting the site name in a repeated "},{"type":"text","text":"<h1>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is a common mistake that confuses the document outline."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Lists: ul, ol, dl"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The three list types each carry distinct meaning:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- ul: unordered — items have no inherent sequence -->\n<ul>\n  <li>Supports TypeScript out of the box</li>\n  <li>Built-in image optimization</li>\n  <li>File-based routing</li>\n</ul>\n\n<!-- ol: ordered — sequence matters -->\n<ol>\n  <li>Install Node.js (v18+)</li>\n  <li>Run: npx create-next-app@latest</li>\n  <li>cd into the project folder</li>\n  <li>Run: npm run dev</li>\n</ol>\n\n<!-- dl: description list — term/definition pairs -->\n<dl>\n  <dt>SSR</dt>\n  <dd>Server-Side Rendering — page generated per request on the server</dd>\n  <dt>SSG</dt>\n  <dd>Static Site Generation — page pre-rendered at build time</dd>\n  <dt>ISR</dt>\n  <dd>Incremental Static Regeneration — static pages regenerated in the background</dd>\n</dl>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Never use a list purely for visual indentation. Never use "},{"type":"text","text":"<br>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" tags to simulate paragraph breaks — use actual "},{"type":"text","text":"<p>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" elements."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"figure and figcaption"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When an image, diagram, code example, or table is referenced from the surrounding text as a self-contained unit, wrap it in "},{"type":"text","text":"<figure>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" with an optional "},{"type":"text","text":"<figcaption>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<figure>\n  <img\n    src=\"/images/app-router-diagram.png\"\n    alt=\"Diagram showing the Next.js App Router file system structure\"\n    width=\"800\"\n    height=\"450\"\n  >\n  <figcaption>\n    Figure 1: The Next.js App Router maps the <code>app/</code> directory\n    structure directly to URL routes.\n  </figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n<!-- Code listing as a figure -->\n<figure>\n  <figcaption>Fetching data in a Server Component</figcaption>\n  <pre><code>async function Page() {\n  const data = await fetch('/api/data').then(r => r.json())\n  return &lt;pre&gt;{JSON.stringify(data, null, 2)}&lt;/pre&gt;\n}</code></pre>\n</figure>"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Semantic HTML in Next.js Components"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In a Next.js application, semantic HTML is written inside React components exactly as in plain HTML. JSX renders to the same HTML elements — the component model does not change element semantics."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"tsx"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// components/BlogPost.tsx\ntype Post = {\n  title: string\n  author: string\n  publishedAt: string\n  excerpt: string\n  content: string\n  tags: string[]\n}\n\nexport function BlogPost({ post }: { post: Post }) {\n  return (\n    <article>\n      <header>\n        <h1>{post.title}</h1>\n        <p>\n          By {post.author} ·{' '}\n          <time dateTime={post.publishedAt}>\n            {new Date(post.publishedAt).toLocaleDateString('en-US', {\n              year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric',\n            })}\n          </time>\n        </p>\n      </header>\n\n      <p className=\"lead\">{post.excerpt}</p>\n\n      <div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: post.content }} />\n\n      <footer>\n        <ul aria-label=\"Tags\">\n          {post.tags.map(tag => (\n            <li key={tag}>\n              <a href={`/tag/${tag}`}>{tag}</a>\n            </li>\n          ))}\n        </ul>\n      </footer>\n    </article>\n  )\n}"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Root Layout with Skip Link"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"tsx"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// app/layout.tsx\nexport default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {\n  return (\n    <html lang=\"en\">\n      <body>\n        {/* Visible on focus — lets keyboard users skip to main content */}\n        <a href=\"#main-content\" className=\"skip-link\">\n          Skip to main content\n        </a>\n        <header>\n          <nav aria-label=\"Main navigation\">\n            {/* site nav */}\n          </nav>\n        </header>\n        <main id=\"main-content\">\n          {children}\n        </main>\n        <footer>\n          <nav aria-label=\"Footer links\">\n            {/* footer nav */}\n          </nav>\n        </footer>\n      </body>\n    </html>\n  )\n}"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"css"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":".skip-link {\n  position: absolute;\n  top: -40px;\n  left: 0;\n  padding: 8px 16px;\n  background: #0070f3;\n  color: white;\n  z-index: 1000;\n  transition: top 0.1s;\n}\n.skip-link:focus {\n  top: 0;\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skip link is hidden off-screen until focused. When a keyboard user presses Tab on page load, it becomes the first focusable element and becomes visible, letting them jump over the navigation directly to "},{"type":"text","text":"<main>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Mistakes"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Div soup — using div for everything"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- ❌ Conveys nothing to assistive tech or search engines -->\n<div class=\"header\">\n  <div class=\"nav\">\n    <div class=\"nav-item\"><a href=\"/\">Home</a></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"content\">\n  <div class=\"article\">\n    <div class=\"title\">My Blog Post</div>\n    <div class=\"body\">Content here...</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- ✅ Semantic structure describes each region's role -->\n<header>\n  <nav aria-label=\"Main navigation\">\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </nav>\n</header>\n<main>\n  <article>\n    <h1>My Blog Post</h1>\n    <p>Content here...</p>\n  </article>\n</main>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Choosing heading levels for visual size"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- ❌ Using h3 because it \"looks right\" — breaks the document outline -->\n<h1>My Blog</h1>\n<h3>Latest Post</h3>   <!-- skips h2 -->\n<h3>About Me</h3>\n\n<!-- ✅ Logical hierarchy; control visual size with CSS -->\n<h1>My Blog</h1>\n<h2>Latest Post</h2>\n<h2>About Me</h2>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Using b and i instead of strong and em"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- ❌ Visual-only: bold and italic with no semantic meaning -->\n<p>Do <b>not</b> click this button unless you are sure.</p>\n<p>You must complete this <i>today</i>.</p>\n\n<!-- ✅ Semantic meaning: strong = important; em = stress emphasis -->\n<p>Do <strong>not</strong> click this button unless you are sure.</p>\n<p>You must complete this <em>today</em>.</p>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple h1 elements on a page"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- ❌ Multiple h1s — screen readers cannot identify the page's primary topic -->\n<h1>Acme Inc</h1>      <!-- site name -->\n<h1>Blog</h1>          <!-- page title -->\n<h1>Latest Posts</h1>  <!-- section heading -->\n\n<!-- ✅ One h1 per page; site name belongs in <title> metadata -->\n<h1>Blog — Latest Posts</h1>\n<h2>This Week</h2>\n<h2>Last Month</h2>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Using section as a generic div"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"html"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!-- ❌ section without a heading — not a real semantic section -->\n<section class=\"card-wrapper\">\n  <section class=\"card\">\n    <p>Card content</p>\n  </section>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ✅ div for presentational wrappers; section for real thematic groups -->\n<div class=\"card-wrapper\">\n  <article class=\"card\">\n    <h2>Card Title</h2>\n    <p>Card content</p>\n  </article>\n</div>"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Semantic HTML","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]},{"type":"text","text":" means choosing elements for their meaning, not their default visual appearance. Use CSS to control visual style."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Landmark elements ("},{"type":"text","text":"<header>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<main>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<article>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<section>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<aside>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","text":"<footer>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":") give screen readers and search engines structural context."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A page has exactly one "},{"type":"text","text":"<main>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"type":"text","text":"<header>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","text":"<footer>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" can appear at any sectioning level, not only at the page level."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple "},{"type":"text","text":"<nav>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" elements on one page each need a distinct "},{"type":"text","text":"aria-label","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Heading levels ("},{"type":"text","text":"<h1>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":"–"},{"type":"text","text":"<h6>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":") form the document outline. Never skip levels. One "},{"type":"text","text":"<h1>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" per page; site name goes in "},{"type":"text","text":"<title>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<strong>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" conveys importance; "},{"type":"text","text":"<em>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" conveys stress emphasis. "},{"type":"text","text":"<b>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","text":"<i>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are visual-only — use the semantic versions."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","text":"<time datetime=\"...\">","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" for dates and times so machines can parse them reliably."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In Next.js, semantic HTML is written inside React/JSX components normally. The component model does not alter element semantics."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Include a skip link ("},{"type":"text","text":"<a href=\"#main-content\">Skip to main content</a>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":") as the first focusable element in the root layout."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<figure>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","text":"<figcaption>","marks":[{"type":"code"}]},{"type":"text","text":" mark referenced, self-contained content units like images, diagrams, and code listings."}]}]}]}]}}